<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idb7d465f4-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea" identifier="/us/usc/t5/s606"><num value="606">§ 606.</num><heading> Effect on other law</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The requirements of sections 603 and 604 of this title do not alter in any manner standards otherwise applicable by law to agency action.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idb7d465f5-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea">(Added <ref href="/us/pl/96/354/s3/a">Pub. L. 96–354, § 3(a)</ref>, <date date="1980-09-19">Sept. 19, 1980</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/94/1168">94 Stat. 1168</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
